<subSubSection id="A1E247EDFFDFFFBBFF7AFB76FAFDFAC5" pageId="15" pageNumber="100" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E9471466FFDFFFBBFF7AFB76FAFDFAC5" blockId="15.[151,1439,810,1322]" pageId="15" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis id="DB8CC874FFDFFFBBFF7AFB76FED9FB30" bold="true" box="[198,312,1221,1247]" pageId="15" pageNumber="100">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species was described on the basis of 
<specimenCount id="FFFEDFEFFFDFFFBBFCF4FB76FC30FB30" box="[840,977,1221,1247]" pageId="15" pageNumber="100" type="female">four female</specimenCount>
specimens, thus the male morphology has not been previously described. The present report represents for the first time that the endopod of male first pleopod possesses a distomesial acute appendix interna similar to those of congeneric species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
